{##
 # MCP AI Integration — connection info shown above the addon settings form.
 #
 # Markup mirrors the native X-Cart admin options form (ul.table.default-table,
 # table-label / table-value, input-field-wrapper, form-control field__field,
 # btn regular-button) so the block reads as a native part of the page instead
 # of a self-styled card. Only the few rules the platform does not provide
 # (monospace readonly fields, secret masking, test-result colours) are kept.
 #}
{% set webDir = config.Security.web_dir|default('') %}
{% set currentKey = this.getMcpApiKey()|default('') %}

<div class="mcp-connection has-tips">
  <h2 class="mcp-connection-title">{{ t('Connect an AI client') }}</h2>
  <p class="mcp-connection-lead">{{ t('Use the values below to connect Claude, Cursor, Codex or any MCP client to this store.') }}</p>

  <ul class="table default-table mcp-connection-list">

    <li class="input input-text">
      <div class="table-label">
        <label for="mcp-endpoint">{{ t('HTTP Endpoint') }}</label>
      </div>
      <div class="table-value">
        <div class="input-internal-wrapper">
          <div class="mcp-field">
            <span class="input-field-wrapper input input-text">
              <input type="text" id="mcp-endpoint" class="form-control field__field mcp-mono" value="{{ webDir }}/mcp" readonly onclick="this.select()" />
            </span>
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button mcp-copy" data-copy="#mcp-endpoint">{{ t('Copy') }}</button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="input input-text">
      <div class="table-label">
        <label for="mcp-apikey">{{ t('API Key') }}</label>
      </div>
      <div class="table-value">
        <div class="input-internal-wrapper">
          {% if currentKey %}
            <div class="mcp-field">
              <span class="input-field-wrapper input input-text">
                <input type="text" id="mcp-apikey" class="form-control field__field mcp-mono mcp-secret" value="{{ currentKey }}" readonly onclick="this.select()" />
              </span>
              <button type="button" class="btn regular-button mcp-copy" data-copy="#mcp-apikey">{{ t('Copy') }}</button>
              <button type="button" class="btn regular-button mcp-reveal">{{ t('Show') }}</button>
            </div>
          {% else %}
            <span class="mcp-muted">{{ t('Not set — falls back to X-Cart API keys from the database.') }}</span>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="input input-textarea">
      <div class="table-label">
        <label for="mcp-json">{{ t('Client config (JSON)') }}</label>
      </div>
      <div class="table-value">
        <div class="input-internal-wrapper">
          <span class="input-field-wrapper input input-textarea">
            <textarea id="mcp-json" class="form-control field__field mcp-mono" readonly rows="8" onclick="this.select()">{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "type": "streamable-http",
      "url": "__MCP_ENDPOINT__",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer {{ currentKey|default('YOUR_API_KEY') }}" }
    }
  }
}</textarea>
          </span>
          <div class="mcp-actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button mcp-copy" data-copy="#mcp-json">{{ t('Copy JSON') }}</button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="input input-textarea">
      <div class="table-label">
        <label for="mcp-prompt">{{ t('AI Agent Setup Prompt') }}</label>
      </div>
      <div class="table-value">
        <div class="input-internal-wrapper">
          <p class="mcp-help">{{ t('Paste into your AI assistant and it will connect this MCP server for you.') }}</p>
          <span class="input-field-wrapper input input-textarea">
            <textarea id="mcp-prompt" class="form-control field__field mcp-mono" readonly rows="12" onclick="this.select()">Please connect my AI client to an X-Cart store over the Model Context Protocol (MCP).

Server:
- Transport: Streamable HTTP
- Endpoint URL: __MCP_ENDPOINT__
- Authentication: HTTP header  Authorization: Bearer {{ currentKey|default('YOUR_API_KEY') }}

Do the following:
1. If my client supports remote / streamable-HTTP MCP servers (Cursor, Codex, VS Code), add this server to its MCP configuration:
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "type": "streamable-http",
      "url": "__MCP_ENDPOINT__",
      "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer {{ currentKey|default('YOUR_API_KEY') }}" }
    }
  }
}

2. If my client only supports local STDIO servers (e.g. Claude Desktop), use the mcp-remote bridge (requires Node.js / npx):
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "xcart": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "__MCP_ENDPOINT__", "--header", "Authorization:${XCART_MCP_AUTH}"],
      "env": { "XCART_MCP_AUTH": "Bearer {{ currentKey|default('YOUR_API_KEY') }}" }
    }
  }
}

3. After updating the config, restart the client, then verify by listing the available MCP tools. This server manages products, orders, categories, reports, vehicle fitment, brands and supplier category mapping (ASAP / Turn14 / SEMA Data).

Treat the API key as a secret — do not share or commit it.</textarea>
          </span>
          <div class="mcp-actions">
            <button type="button" class="btn regular-button mcp-copy" data-copy="#mcp-prompt">{{ t('Copy as prompt') }}</button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="input">
      <div class="table-label">
        <label>{{ t('Status') }}</label>
      </div>
      <div class="table-value">
        <div class="input-internal-wrapper">
          <button type="button" class="btn regular-button" id="mcp-test">{{ t('Test connection') }}</button>
          <span id="mcp-test-result" class="mcp-test-result"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="clear"></div>
      </div>
    </li>

  </ul>
</div>

<script>
(function () {
  var root = document.querySelector('.mcp-connection');
  if (!root || root.dataset.mcpBooted) return;
  root.dataset.mcpBooted = '1';

  var webDir = '{{ webDir|e('js') }}';
  var endpoint = location.origin + webDir + '/mcp';
  var apiKey = '{{ currentKey|default('')|e('js') }}';

  // Substitute the absolute endpoint everywhere (web_dir alone may be relative).
  var epInput = document.getElementById('mcp-endpoint');
  if (epInput) epInput.value = endpoint;
  ['mcp-json', 'mcp-prompt'].forEach(function (id) {
    var el = document.getElementById(id);
    if (el) el.value = el.value.split('__MCP_ENDPOINT__').join(endpoint);
  });

  function flash(btn, text) {
    var orig = btn.textContent;
    btn.textContent = text;
    setTimeout(function () { btn.textContent = orig; }, 1500);
  }

  root.querySelectorAll('.mcp-copy').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var el = document.querySelector(btn.getAttribute('data-copy'));
      if (!el) return;
      var val = el.value;
      var done = function () { flash(btn, '{{ t('Copied!')|e('js') }}'); };
      if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(val).then(done, function () { el.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); done(); });
      } else { el.select(); document.execCommand('copy'); done(); }
    });
  });

  var revealBtn = root.querySelector('.mcp-reveal');
  if (revealBtn) {
    revealBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var f = document.getElementById('mcp-apikey');
      if (!f) return;
      f.classList.toggle('mcp-secret');
      revealBtn.textContent = f.classList.contains('mcp-secret') ? '{{ t('Show')|e('js') }}' : '{{ t('Hide')|e('js') }}';
    });
  }

  var testBtn = document.getElementById('mcp-test');
  if (testBtn) {
    testBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var result = document.getElementById('mcp-test-result');
      testBtn.disabled = true;
      testBtn.textContent = '{{ t('Testing...')|e('js') }}';
      result.textContent = '';
      var headers = { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' };
      if (apiKey) headers['Authorization'] = 'Bearer ' + apiKey;
      fetch(endpoint, { method: 'POST', headers: headers, body: JSON.stringify({
        jsonrpc: '2.0', id: 1, method: 'initialize',
        params: { protocolVersion: '2025-03-26', capabilities: {}, clientInfo: { name: 'X-Cart Admin Test', version: '1.0.0' } }
      }) })
        .then(function (r) { return r.json(); })
        .then(function (data) {
          if (data.result && data.result.serverInfo) {
            result.className = 'mcp-test-result mcp-ok';
            result.textContent = '✓ ' + data.result.serverInfo.name + ' v' + data.result.serverInfo.version;
          } else {
            result.className = 'mcp-test-result mcp-err';
            result.textContent = (data.error && data.error.message) || data.error || '{{ t('Unexpected response')|e('js') }}';
          }
        })
        .catch(function (err) {
          result.className = 'mcp-test-result mcp-err';
          result.textContent = '{{ t('Connection failed')|e('js') }}' + ': ' + err.message;
        })
        .finally(function () {
          testBtn.disabled = false;
          testBtn.textContent = '{{ t('Test connection')|e('js') }}';
        });
    });
  }
})();
</script>

<style>
/* Typography/colours come from the native admin theme. The flex row + 270px
 * label column mirror the native options form (whose layout is scoped to
 * .model-properties, which this header widget sits outside of) so the block
 * lines up with the settings form below it. Only gaps the theme can't fill
 * are styled here. */
.mcp-connection { margin: 0 0 24px; }
.mcp-connection-title { margin: 0 0 4px; }
.mcp-connection-lead { margin: 0 0 14px; opacity: .75; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-connection-list { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
.mcp-connection ul.table li.input { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; padding: 8px 0; }
.mcp-connection ul.table li.input .table-label { flex: 0 0 270px; width: 270px; box-sizing: border-box; padding: 6px 15px 0 0; text-align: right; }
.mcp-connection ul.table li.input .table-value { flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 0; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-help { margin: 0 0 6px; font-weight: 400; opacity: .7; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-mono { font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 12px; }
.mcp-connection .input-internal-wrapper { min-width: 0; }
.mcp-connection .input-field-wrapper { display: block; min-width: 0; }
.mcp-connection .input-field-wrapper .form-control { width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box; }
.mcp-connection textarea.mcp-mono { width: 100%; max-width: 100%; box-sizing: border-box; resize: vertical; }
/* Field + inline action buttons: native white/blue regular-button, no bootstrap
 * input-group (its context recolours the buttons grey). min-width:0 lets the
 * long readonly value shrink instead of forcing horizontal page overflow. */
.mcp-connection .mcp-field { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 8px; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-field .input-field-wrapper { flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 0; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-field .btn { flex: 0 0 auto; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-actions { margin-top: 6px; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-secret { -webkit-text-security: disc; text-security: disc; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-muted { opacity: .65; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-test-result { margin-left: 10px; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-test-result.mcp-ok { color: #2d8c3c; font-weight: 600; }
.mcp-connection .mcp-test-result.mcp-err { color: #c0392b; }
</style>
